A gangland killer given the longest jail term in Scottish history has escaped punishment for having a mobile phone in jail - because a new sentence wouldn't start until 2038. Killer escapes punishment for jail phone A gangland killer given the longest jail term in Scottish history has escaped punishment for having a mobile phone in jail - because a new sentence wouldn't start until 2038.Hitman James McDonald has been caught repeatedly with mobile phones but escaped any punishment because it would take a quarter of a century to kick in.McDonald, 41, who was locked up for 35 years in 2008, was admonished at Perth Sheriff Court.McDonald and his co-accused Raymond Anderson, 52, were found guilty of murdering Michael Lyons at a Glasgow garage in 2006. 